13/04/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Following talks with Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski in Brussels Tuesday (12 April), EU security chief Javier Solana voiced expectations that the name dispute between Greece and Macedonia would be resolved within months. Addressing a joint news conference after the talks, Solana said the problem should have been resolved long ago and expressed hope that demonstrations of goodwill on both sides would result in a compromise during UN-sponsored negotiations. (Macedonian Government Web site, Makfax - 13/04/05; A1 TV, Makfax - 12/04/05)
